# known:
1. In a 30-60-90 triangle, the hypotenuse is always the side opposite the $90^\circ$ angle. Make sure you identify which given side is the hypotenuse before applying side ratios.
2. When decomposing a side like $AD$ into $AE + ED$, remember that $ED$ may come from a different 30-60-90 triangle than $AB$; do not assume $AD = AE$ or reuse $AB$ as $AD$ without geometric justification.
